<item>
            <title>[LU-362] lu_kmem_init() needs error handling</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-362</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Originally this issue was duplicate of &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-760&quot; title=&quot;Test failure on test suite sanity, subtest test_180a&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-760&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-760&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; as mentioned in comments. Now it is about just memleaks. If echo client is failed to set up there are memleaks detected. They are caused by lack of error handling in some function including lu_kmem_init() itself. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
